Research Analyst		JMC Capital Partners		Greater Boston Area		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p>JMC Capital Partners is seeking a skilled research analyst to assist in procuring market information to drive Business Development efforts and investment decisions.  The position will work with the existing BD staff to search out new platform investment opportunities and qualify new market sectors through research efforts and criteria documentation. </p><p></p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong> </p><ul><li>Research markets in which JMC is currently established to identify new acquisition targets for new platforms and add-ons to existing platforms </li><li>Identify new platform markets that meet JMC criteria using the existing matrix </li><li>Create a target lists and company profiles </li><li>Build and maintain relationships with service providers and consultants related to research activities </li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications</strong> </p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree </li><li>Post graduate work experience </li><li>High level of research and data mining skills </li><li>Previous experience conducting research from primary and secondary sources </li><li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills </li><li>Strong interpersonal skills </li><li>Able to work both independently and as part of a team </li></ul><p>$50k annually, medical, dental, vacation and other benefits</p></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p>Founded in 1999, JMC has developed a proven track record of extraordinary returns through the execution of their Industrial “Platform Strategy”. The partners have more than 75 years of combined experience as investors, owners, and senior executives of successful industrial businesses. We have personally invested in every transaction and have the experience, skills and vision to build profitable and strategically well-positioned businesses. Our focused area of investment is US based industrial product driven companies that can demonstrate potential for sustainable and stable growth. At JMC, we are control investors and build very profitable, industrial products companies with revenues in excess of $100MM, through the integration of like companies onto a common Platform. Through the execution of the Platform Strategy we are able to take advantage of operational economies of scale and cross selling of acquired product lines. The Platform Strategy significantly mitigates investment risk and allows JMC to greatly influence the value of our portfolio companies.</p></div>